<br>
My only advice about a point system is.... do not think short term.  Plan ahead, and incorporate mechanisms for adjustment as EQ and your guild changes.  Something worth X today will not be worth X tomorrow when an upgrade for that slot is discovered. How are your guild members going to deal with that?  Change the point value? Retroactively for everyone who has X already? Or keep it the same and just make the new item Y worth 1 point more? Is the value of Y going to piss off the person who looted X yesterday?  What happens when X drops tomorrow, but ppl now don't want it because Y is better? Is X going to rot now? Will the guild get mad at members who don't want to loot X because those members are waiting for Y now?  But what about Z? I heard it's 5 times better than Y... should I wait for that instead?  If you were holding a gun, and I was 10 feet across from you, how many times would you pull the trigger right now?<br>
